                "img": "https://arxiv.org/html/2606.24231/2606.24231v1/x1.png",
                "caption": "Figure 1:Comparison of multimodal planning paradigms. (a) Scoring-based methods select from a large fixed trajectory vocabulary. (b) Anchor-based methods decode multiple proposals from action anchors and sparsely supervise them with GT. (c) Our method FlowR2A learns the reward-conditioned action distributionp​(a|r)p(a|r)from dense trajectories, whereaais the action andrris the reward. Red lines indicate training supervision.",
                "position": 303
            }
